<assessmentItem xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1 http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/qti/qtiv2p1/imsqti_v2p1p1.xsd http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML http://www.w3.org/Math/XMLSchema/mathml2/mathml2.xsd" identifier="idf9a97d8b-8782-4866-a275-4abaed71b05f" title="ableitung_potenzen_02" adaptive="false" timeDependent="false"><responseDeclaration identifier="RESPONSE_1408973036384" cardinality="single" baseType="string" /><outcomeDeclaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" baseType="float"><defaultValue><value>0</value></defaultValue></outcomeDeclaration><outcomeDeclaration identifier="MAXSCORE" cardinality="single" baseType="float"><defaultValue><value>1</value></defaultValue></outcomeDeclaration><outcomeDeclaration identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC" cardinality="single" baseType="identifier" view="testConstructor"><defaultValue><value>empty</value></defaultValue></outcomeDeclaration><outcomeDeclaration identifier="FEEDBACKMODAL" cardinality="multiple" baseType="identifier" view="testConstructor" /><templateProcessing><setCorrectResponse identifier="RESPONSE_1408973036384"><customOperator definition="VARIABLESTRING" value="" /></setCorrectResponse></templateProcessing><itemBody ><p>Geben Sie die Ableitung der Funktion $$f(x) = x^x$$ an! Bitte vereinfachen Sie Ihre Lösung soweit wie möglich.</p><p><strong>Ergebnis:</strong> $$f'(x) = $$<textEntryInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE_1408973036384" class="maxima-formula show-latex" /></p><p> </p><p>Hinweise zur Formeleingabe:</p><ul><li>\(\frac{x}{y}\) = x/y, \(x^y\) = x^y, \(\ln x=\) log(x)</li><li>\(x\cdot y\) = x*y, z.B. \(3x\) = 3*x  \(\Rightarrow\) Bitte keine * vergessen!</li><li>Durch Klicken auf die ?-Schaltfläche können Sie Ihre Formel vor Speichern der Antwort zunächst überprüfen.</li></ul></itemBody><responseProcessing><responseCondition><responseIf><customOperator definition="MAXIMA" value="is(equal(ev($(1)),ev(x^x*(log(x) + 1))));"><variable identifier="RESPONSE_1408973036384" /><correct identifier="RESPONSE_1408973036384" /></customOperator><setOutcomeValue identifier="SCORE"><sum><variable identifier="SCORE" /><baseValue baseType="float">1</baseValue></sum></setOutcomeValue></responseIf></responseCondition><responseCondition><responseIf><not><isNull><variable identifier="RESPONSE_1408973036384" /></isNull></not><setOutcomeValue identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC"><baseValue baseType="identifier">incorrect</baseValue></setOutcomeValue></responseIf></responseCondition><responseCondition><responseIf><and><not><match><variable identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC" /><baseValue baseType="identifier">empty</baseValue></match></not><equal toleranceMode="exact"><variable identifier="SCORE" /><variable identifier="MAXSCORE" /></equal></and><setOutcomeValue identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC"><baseValue baseType="identifier">correct</baseValue></setOutcomeValue></responseIf></responseCondition><responseCondition><responseIf><and><match><baseValue baseType="identifier">correct</baseValue><variable identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC" /></match></and><setOutcomeValue identifier="FEEDBACKMODAL"><multiple><variable identifier="FEEDBACKMODAL" /><baseValue baseType="identifier">Feedback1702968553</baseValue></multiple></setOutcomeValue></responseIf></responseCondition><responseCondition><responseIf><and><match><baseValue baseType="identifier">incorrect</baseValue><variable identifier="FEEDBACKBASIC" /></match></and><setOutcomeValue identifier="FEEDBACKMODAL"><multiple><variable identifier="FEEDBACKMODAL" /><baseValue baseType="identifier">Feedback1518712040</baseValue></multiple></setOutcomeValue></responseIf></responseCondition></responseProcessing><modalFeedback  identifier="Feedback1702968553" outcomeIdentifier="FEEDBACKMODAL" showHide="show" title="Richtig!" /><modalFeedback  identifier="Feedback1518712040" outcomeIdentifier="FEEDBACKMODAL" showHide="show" title="Beachte:"><p>$$\qquad\qquad\qquad x^x = \mathrm e^{\displaystyle \ln{x^x}} = \mathrm e^{\displaystyle x \cdot \ln x}$$, da $$\mathrm e^{\displaystyle\ln x} = x$$.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Lösung:</strong> $$\qquad f'(x) = \Big(\mathrm e^{\displaystyle x \cdot \ln x}\Big)' = \mathrm e^{\displaystyle x \cdot \ln x} \cdot \Big(1 \cdot \ln x + x \cdot \frac{1}{x}\Big) = x^x \cdot (\ln x +1)$$.</p></modalFeedback></assessmentItem>
